                    <a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/42256412/"><img src="https://img3.doubanio.com/view/page_note/small/public/p42256412-1.jpg"></a>
                  </div>
                  <span class="">'Absence of good' There's no bad, which is only the absence of good. Thus, bad is just 'imperfection'. I always believe that there are no good and bad, cuz it's hard to determine and define.</span>
                <p class="pl">
                  <span class="">2017-03-11 12:08</span>
                  
                </p>
